Question: A Magento store owner wants to automatically modify the meta descriptions of all products by adding "Sell" at the beginning and "Here" at the end. Which of the following code snippets would correctly accomplish this task?

A) 
```php
$products = Mage::getModel('catalog/product')->getCollection();
$products->addAttributeToSelect('meta_description');

foreach ($products as $product) {
    $product->setMetaDescription('Sell '.$product->getMetaDescription().' Here');
    $product->save();
}
```

B) 
```php
$products = Mage::getModel('catalog/product')->getCollection();
$products->addAttributeToSelect('meta_description');

foreach ($products as $product) {
    $product->setMetaDescription('Sell '.$product->getMetaDescription().' Here');
    $product->getResource()->saveAttribute($product, 'meta_description');
}
```

C) 
```php
$products = Mage::getModel('catalog/product')->getCollection();
$products->addAttributeToSelect('meta_title');

foreach ($products as $product) {
    $product->setMetaTitle('Sell '.$product->getMetaTitle().' Here');
    $product->getResource()->saveAttribute($product, 'meta_title');
}
```

D) 
```php
$products = Mage::getModel('catalog/product')->getCollection();
$products->addAttributeToSelect('meta_description');

foreach ($products as $product) {
    $newDescription = 'Sell '.$product->getMetaDescription().' Here';
    $product->setData('meta_description', $newDescription);
    $product->save();
}
```

Correct Answer: B

Explanation: Option B is the correct answer because it efficiently modifies the meta description for all products. It uses the `getResource()->saveAttribute()` method, which is faster than calling `save()` on the entire product model. It also correctly selects and modifies the 'meta_description' attribute, which is likely the correct attribute for meta descriptions in Magento.

Option A is close but uses the slower `save()` method. Option C incorrectly modifies the 'meta_title' instead of 'meta_description'. Option D, while it would work, also uses the slower `save()` method and unnecessarily creates a new variable for the description.

