Here's a multi-choice question based on the provided information:

Question: You have a Backbone.js application that displays categories and products from a JSON file. You want to update the view automatically when the JSON data changes without manually refreshing the page. Which of the following approaches would be the most effective way to achieve this?

A) Add a setInterval() function in the initialize method of the view to re-render every 10 seconds.

B) Implement a WebSocket connection to receive real-time updates from the server when the JSON file changes.

C) Use the Backbone.js built-in sync() method to periodically check for changes in the JSON file.

D) Add an event listener to the collection that triggers a re-render when the fetch() method completes successfully.

Correct Answer: D

Explanation:
Option A is inefficient as it would re-render the view every 10 seconds regardless of whether the data has changed or not. This could lead to unnecessary processing and potential performance issues.

Option B, while effective for real-time updates, is overly complex for this scenario and would require significant changes to both the client and server-side code.

Option C is not a standard Backbone.js method and would require custom implementation, potentially leading to inefficient polling of the server.

Option D is the most appropriate solution in this context. By adding an event listener to the collection, you can trigger a re-render only when new data is successfully fetched. This approach is efficient and aligns well with Backbone.js's event-driven architecture. You could implement this by modifying the view as follows:

```javascript
var CategoriesView = Backbone.View.extend({ 
    initialize: function () {
        this.categories = new Categories();
        this.listenTo(this.categories, 'sync', this.render);
        this.categories.fetch();
    },
    render: function () {
        var template = _.template($('#categories-template').html(), {categories: this.categories.models});
        this.$el.html(template);
        return this;
    }
});
```

This solution will update the view whenever the collection is successfully synced with the server, ensuring that the displayed data is always up-to-date without unnecessary re-renders.

